name: Furina
about: Furina de Fontaine is a playable Hydro character in Genshin Impact, initially introduced as the flamboyant and prideful Hydro Archon. Later revealed to be a public persona, she transitions to a humbler life as an actress and artistic consultant. Her ability to switch between Pneuma and Ousia states makes her versatile in combat, excelling as a Sub-DPS with strong support capabilities. Furina's theatrical demeanor hides a deep sense of responsibility for Fontaine's people.

name: Hu Tao
about: Hu Tao is a playable Pyro character in Genshin Impact, serving as the 77th Director of the Wangsheng Funeral Parlor in Liyue. Known for her eccentric and cheerful personality, she hides a serious dedication to her duties, ensuring the balance between life and death. A talented poet, her works are cherished by Liyue's citizens. In combat, Hu Tao excels as a Main DPS, dealing high Pyro damage with her polearm.

name: Ganyu
about: Ganyu is a playable Cryo character in Genshin Impact, a half-qilin adeptus serving as the general secretary of the Liyue Qixing. Bound by a contract with the Geo Archon Morax, she handles administrative duties with diligence. Her adeptus heritage makes her feel distant from humans, causing social awkwardness. In battle, Ganyu is a powerful Main DPS, utilizing her charged bow attacks to deal massive Cryo damage.

name: Keqing
about: Keqing is a playable Electro character in Genshin Impact, serving as the Yuheng of the Liyue Qixing. Known for her skepticism toward divine rule, she believes in human self-reliance and works tirelessly to modernize Liyue. Her pragmatic and decisive nature makes her a respected leader. In combat, Keqing excels as a Main DPS, delivering fast and powerful Electro attacks with her sword.

name: Raiden Shogun
about: Raiden Shogun, also known as Ei, is a playable Electro character in Genshin Impact and the Electro Archon of Inazuma. Ruling with an iron fist to achieve eternity, she resides in the Plane of Euthymia, using a puppet to govern. Her pursuit of eternity stems from personal loss, making her a complex figure. In battle, she is a formidable Main DPS, dealing massive Electro damage.

name: Yae Miko
about: Yae Miko is a playable Electro character in Genshin Impact, serving as the Guuji of the Grand Narukami Shrine and Raiden Shogun's familiar. A cunning and witty kitsune, she oversees Inazuma's cultural affairs and runs the Yae Publishing House. Her playful demeanor hides a sharp intellect. In combat, Yae Miko excels as a Sub-DPS, deploying totems for consistent Electro damage.

name: Clorinde
about: Clorinde is a playable Electro character in Genshin Impact, known as Fontaine's strongest Champion Duelist. Serving as Furina's bodyguard, she upholds justice with unmatched swordsmanship. Her serious demeanor and loyalty to Fontaine define her character. In battle, Clorinde shines as a Main DPS, combining swift sword strikes with Electro-infused attacks for high damage output. // Add the config plugin to your app config file. name: Citlali
about: Citlali is a playable Cryo character in Genshin Impact, hailing from Natlan. As a member of the Shadowseekers, she uses her Cryo abilities to support her allies in battle. Little is known about her background, but her calm and strategic nature makes her a valuable team member. As a Support, Citlali enhances team performance with Cryo shields and buffs, ideal for elemental reactions.

name: Chiori
about: Chiori is a playable Geo character in Genshin Impact, a renowned fashion designer from Inazuma who runs the Chioriya Boutique in Fontaine. Her sharp wit and dedication to her craft make her a standout figure. In combat, Chiori excels as a Sub-DPS, using Geo constructs and swift sword attacks to deal consistent damage while supporting her team.

name: Eula
about: Eula is a playable Cryo character in Genshin Impact, a descendant of the Lawrence Clan in Mondstadt. Despite her clan's tarnished reputation, she serves as a Captain in the Knights of Favonius, wielding her claymore with grace. Her rebellious spirit and sense of justice define her. As a Main DPS, Eula delivers devastating Cryo and physical damage with her burst.

name: Escoffier
about: Escoffier is a character in Genshin Impact, mentioned in Fontaine's lore but not yet released as a playable character. Limited information exists about their role, element, or weapon. Speculated to be tied to Fontaine's culinary or cultural scene, Escoffier remains a mystery. Further details are needed to confirm their combat role and abilities.

name: Fischl
about: Fischl is a playable Electro character in Genshin Impact, an eccentric investigator for the Adventurers' Guild in Mondstadt. Accompanied by her raven, Oz, she adopts the persona of 'Prinzessin der Verurteilung' from a fantasy novel. Her dramatic flair hides a kind heart. As a Sub-DPS, Fischl excels at dealing consistent Electro damage through Oz's abilities.

name: Kazuha
about: Kaedehara Kazuha is a playable Anemo character in Genshin Impact, a wandering samurai from Inazuma with a poetic soul. After losing his clan, he joins the Crux Fleet, using his Anemo abilities to sense nature's rhythms. His calm demeanor hides a fierce resolve. As a Support, Kazuha boosts elemental damage and provides crowd control with his swirl reactions.

name: Jean
about: Jean is a playable Anemo character in Genshin Impact, serving as the Acting Grand Master of the Knights of Favonius in Mondstadt. Known for her dedication to protecting the city, she is a selfless leader who prioritizes duty. Her healing and crowd-control abilities make her a versatile Support, capable of cleansing debuffs and boosting team survivability with her Anemo-based skills. Jean's calm and composed nature hides a strong sense of responsibility.

name: Kamisato Ayaka
about: Kamisato Ayaka is a playable Cryo character in Genshin Impact, the eldest daughter of the Kamisato Clan and a key figure in Inazuma's Yashiro Commission. Known for her elegance and grace, she upholds her family's honor while navigating political challenges. As a Main DPS, Ayaka excels in dealing Cryo damage with her charged attacks and powerful Elemental Burst, making her a top choice for Freeze and Permafrost teams.

name: Kinich
about: Kinich is a playable Dendro character in Genshin Impact, a swift and agile warrior from Natlan. Known for his fast-paced claymore playstyle, he stands out among other claymore users with his unique mobility and Dendro application. Kinich's abilities focus on dealing high Dendro damage, making him a strong Main DPS for teams centered around Bloom and Hyperbloom reactions. His adventurous spirit defines his role in Natlan's lore.

name: Kirara
about: Kirara is a playable Dendro character in Genshin Impact, a nekomata courier working for Inazuma's Komaniya Express. Her playful and energetic personality, combined with her cat-like traits, makes her a fan favorite. As a Support, Kirara provides shields and Dendro application, enhancing Bloom and Hyperbloom teams. Her ability to climb and explore efficiently also makes her valuable for exploration in Teyvat.

name: Klee
about: Klee is a playable Pyro character in Genshin Impact, a young member of the Knights of Favonius known for her love of explosives. Despite her childlike demeanor, she wields powerful Pyro attacks, making her a formidable Main DPS. Her bombs and charged attacks deal massive area-of-effect damage, ideal for Pyro-based teams. Klee's adventurous and mischievous nature often leads to chaos in Mondstadt.

name: Lisa
about: Lisa is a playable Electro character in Genshin Impact, a librarian for the Knights of Favonius and a former Sumeru Akademiya scholar. Known for her laid-back yet intelligent personality, she wields Electro with precision. As a Support, Lisa provides consistent Electro application and energy generation, making her valuable in Overload and Electro-Charged teams. Her knowledge and charm make her a beloved figure in Mondstadt.

name: Layla
about: Layla is a playable Cryo character in Genshin Impact, a student at Sumeru Akademiya known for her sleepwalking tendencies. Despite her shy and anxious nature, she excels at providing Cryo shields and off-field Cryo application. As a Support, Layla enhances Freeze and Melt teams with her reliable shielding and energy generation, making her a valuable addition to many team compositions.

name: Lyney
about: Lyney is a playable Pyro character in Genshin Impact, a charismatic magician from Fontaine and a member of the House of the Hearth. Known for his theatrical flair and loyalty to his sister Lynette, he uses his bow to deliver precise Pyro attacks. As a Main DPS, Lyney excels in dealing high single-target damage, making him ideal for Vaporize and Overload teams.

name: Mavuika
about: Mavuika is a playable Pyro character in Genshin Impact, the Pyro Archon of Natlan. Known for her fierce leadership and unique combat style involving a motorcycle, she delivers devastating Pyro damage. As a Main DPS, Mavuika excels in Vaporize and Overload teams, with her kit relying on allies' attacks to recharge her Ultimate. Her bold design and leadership make her a standout figure.

name: Mualani
about: Mualani is a playable Hydro character in Genshin Impact, a cheerful surfer from Natlan known for her water-based exploration abilities. Her kit focuses on Normal Attacks, delivering high Hydro damage for Vaporize teams. As a Main DPS, Mualani is easy to play and excels in exploration due to her stamina-free water surfing. Her vibrant personality shines in Natlan's lore.

name: Nahida
about: Nahida is a playable Dendro character in Genshin Impact, the Dendro Archon of Sumeru known as the Lesser Lord Kusanali. Despite her childlike appearance, she possesses immense wisdom and compassion. As a Support, Nahida excels in triggering Dendro reactions like Bloom and Hyperbloom, providing off-field damage and Elemental Mastery buffs, making her a cornerstone for Dendro teams.

name: Navia
about: Navia is a playable Geo character in Genshin Impact, the president of the Spina di Rosula in Fontaine. Known for her cheerful yet determined personality, she seeks to uncover the truth behind her father's legacy. As a Main DPS, Navia deals high Geo damage with her claymore, utilizing Crystallize reactions to boost her damage output in Geo-centric teams.

name: Nilou
about: Nilou is a playable Hydro character in Genshin Impact, a dancer from Sumeru's Zubayr Theater. Her graceful performances hide a deep passion for her art. As a Sub-DPS, Nilou excels in Bloom reaction teams, boosting Bountiful Core damage with her Elemental Skill and Burst. Her kit is tailored for Hydro and Dendro synergy, making her a niche but powerful choice.

name: Neuvillette
about: Neuvillette is a playable Hydro character in Genshin Impact, the Chief Justice of Fontaine. Known for his stoic demeanor and sense of justice, he wields immense Hydro power. As a Main DPS, Neuvillette delivers devastating charged attacks and consistent Hydro damage, making him a top choice for Vaporize and Hydro-based teams. His authority shapes Fontaine's legal system.

name: Ororon
about: Ororon is a playable Electro character in Genshin Impact, a member of Natlan's Masters of the Night-Wind. Known for his mysterious and rebellious nature, he uses his bow to support allies with Electro application and buffs. As a Support, Ororon enhances team damage through Electro reactions like Overload and Aggravate, while his mobility aids exploration.

name: Sayu
about: Sayu is a playable Anemo character in Genshin Impact, a ninja from Inazuma's Shuumatsuban. Her small stature and love for napping make her endearing, but she’s a skilled operative. As a Support, Sayu provides healing and Anemo swirl reactions, boosting elemental damage. Her rolling skill aids exploration, making her a versatile addition to many teams.

name: Thoma
about: Thoma is a playable Pyro character in Genshin Impact, a housekeeper for the Kamisato Clan in Inazuma. Originally from Mondstadt, his loyalty and warm personality make him a trusted ally. As a Support, Thoma provides shields and Pyro application, enhancing Vaporize and Overload teams. His protective nature shines in both combat and story.

name: Xiangling
about: Xiangling is a playable Pyro character in Genshin Impact, a passionate chef from Liyue who runs the Wanmin Restaurant. Her culinary experiments often lead to explosive results. As a Sub-DPS, Xiangling excels in off-field Pyro application with her Elemental Burst, making her a staple in Vaporize and Overload teams. Her energy and creativity shine in battle.

name: Xiao
about: Xiao is a playable Anemo character in Genshin Impact, an adeptus and the last Yaksha guarding Liyue. Haunted by his past, he carries a heavy burden but remains fiercely protective. As a Main DPS, Xiao delivers high Anemo damage with his plunge attacks during his Elemental Burst, excelling in hypercarry teams with strong support.

name: Xilonen
about: Xilonen is a playable Geo character in Genshin Impact, a skilled craftswoman from Natlan known for her versatility. As a Support, she provides shields, Elemental Resistance shred, and buffs, making her a game-changer for Geo teams. Her kit enhances elemental reactions and team synergy, while her exploration abilities, like climbing, add utility.

name: Xingqiu
about: Xingqiu is a playable Hydro character in Genshin Impact, a young scholar and heir to the Feiyun Commerce Guild in Liyue. His love for books and chivalry defines his personality. As a Sub-DPS, Xingqiu excels in off-field Hydro application with his Elemental Burst, enabling Vaporize and Freeze reactions. His high energy cost is offset by his utility.

name: Yanfei
about: Yanfei is a playable Pyro character in Genshin Impact, a legal advisor in Liyue with adeptus heritage. Her sharp intellect and fiery personality make her a standout. As a Main DPS, Yanfei delivers consistent Pyro damage with her charged attacks, excelling in Vaporize teams. Her knowledge of law and combat prowess make her a reliable ally.

name: Yelan
about: Yelan is a playable Hydro character in Genshin Impact, a mysterious intelligence agent from Liyue. Known for her cunning and agility, she operates in the shadows. As a Sub-DPS, Yelan provides off-field Hydro application and high damage with her Elemental Burst, rivaling Xingqiu in Vaporize and Freeze teams. Her exploration abilities are also top-tier.

name: Razor
about: Razor is a playable Electro character in Genshin Impact, a boy raised by wolves in Mondstadt's Wolvendom. His feral nature and loyalty to his pack define him. As a Main DPS, Razor excels in dealing physical and Electro damage with his claymore, making him a strong choice for physical damage-focused teams with Superconduct support.

name: Kuki Shinobu
about: Kuki Shinobu is a playable Electro character in Genshin Impact, the deputy leader of the Arataki Gang in Inazuma. A skilled ninja with a calm demeanor, she balances her gang's antics. As a Support, Shinobu provides healing and off-field Electro application, excelling in Hyperbloom and Aggravate teams with her Elemental Mastery-focused kit.

name: Faruzan
about: Faruzan is a playable Anemo character in Genshin Impact, a scholar from Sumeru Akademiya with a passion for ancient mechanics. Trapped for decades, she brings a youthful spirit. As a Support, Faruzan boosts Anemo damage and provides crowd control with her Elemental Burst, making her a key addition to Anemo DPS teams like Xiao.

name: Albedo
about: Albedo is a Geo character in Genshin Impact, serving as the Chief Alchemist of the Knights of Favonius in Mondstadt. Known for his intellect and curiosity, he explores the secrets of the world. As a Sub-DPS, Albedo excels at dealing Geo damage and supporting the team with constructs.

name: Amber
about: Amber is a Pyro character in Genshin Impact, an Outrider for the Knights of Favonius in Mondstadt. Cheerful and energetic, she uses her bow to deal Pyro damage. As a Sub-DPS, Amber supports the team with area-of-effect damage and enemy taunts.

name: Barbara
about: Barbara is a Hydro character in Genshin Impact, a deaconess of the Church of Favonius in Mondstadt. Gentle and musically gifted, she heals her allies. As a Support, Barbara provides strong healing and applies Hydro for elemental reactions.

name: Bennett
about: Bennett is a Pyro character in Genshin Impact, an adventurer leading Benny's Adventure Team in Mondstadt. Despite his bad luck, he remains optimistic. As a Support, Bennett offers healing and attack boosts, making him one of the best support characters.

name: Diluc
about: Diluc is a Pyro character in Genshin Impact, the owner of Dawn Winery in Mondstadt. With a mysterious past, he fights for justice. As a Main DPS, Diluc deals massive Pyro damage with his powerful attacks and burst.

name: Diona
about: Diona is a Cryo character in Genshin Impact, a bartender at Cat's Tail in Mondstadt. Despite disliking alcohol, she excels at mixology. As a Support, Diona provides shields and healing, aiding Cryo-based reactions.

name: Kaeya
about: Kaeya is a Cryo character in Genshin Impact, the Cavalry Captain of the Knights of Favonius. Charismatic yet secretive, he hides many mysteries. As a Sub-DPS, Kaeya deals Cryo damage and supports elemental reactions.

name: Mika
about: Mika is a Cryo character in Genshin Impact, a member of the Knights of Favonius in Mondstadt. A dedicated surveyor, he supports his team. As a Support, Mika provides healing and attack speed buffs, ideal for physical damage teams.

name: Noelle
about: Noelle is a Geo character in Genshin Impact, a maid of the Knights of Favonius in Mondstadt. Hardworking and kind, she dreams of becoming a knight. As a Support, Noelle provides shields and healing, and can act as a Main DPS with the right build.

name: Rosaria
about: Rosaria is a Cryo character in Genshin Impact, a nun of the Church of Favonius in Mondstadt. Cold and pragmatic, she operates in the shadows. As a Sub-DPS, Rosaria deals Cryo damage and boosts the team's critical rate.

name: Sucrose
about: Sucrose is an Anemo character in Genshin Impact, Albedo's assistant in Mondstadt. Shy and studious, she is passionate about research. As a Support, Sucrose provides crowd control and boosts elemental damage through Swirl reactions.

name: Venti
about: Venti is an Anemo character in Genshin Impact, the Anemo Archon Barbatos of Mondstadt. Free-spirited and musical, he loves to play the lyre. As a Support, Venti offers powerful crowd control and energy regeneration, ideal for Swirl-based teams.

name: Baizhu
about: Baizhu is a Dendro character in Genshin Impact, the owner of Bubu Pharmacy in Liyue. Knowledgeable in medicine, he cares for the sick. As a Support, Baizhu provides healing and Dendro application, perfect for Bloom and Hyperbloom teams.

name: Beidou
about: Beidou is an Electro character in Genshin Impact, the captain of the Crux Fleet in Liyue. Bold and charismatic, she leads with strength. As a Sub-DPS, Beidou deals area-of-effect Electro damage and provides shields through counterattacks.

name: Chongyun
about: Chongyun is a Cryo character in Genshin Impact, an exorcist from Liyue. Serious and dedicated, he battles evil spirits. As a Sub-DPS, Chongyun deals Cryo damage and infuses attacks with Cryo, supporting Freeze teams.

name: Ningguang
about: Ningguang is a Geo character in Genshin Impact, the Tianquan of the Liyue Qixing. Intelligent and ambitious, she controls Liyue's commerce. As a Main DPS, Ningguang deals strong Geo damage with her attacks and abilities.

name: Qiqi
about: Qiqi is a Cryo character in Genshin Impact, a zombie working at Bubu Pharmacy in Liyue. Forgetful but adorable, she aids her allies. As a Support, Qiqi provides strong healing and applies Cryo for elemental reactions.

name: Shenhe
about: Shenhe is a Cryo character in Genshin Impact, a disciple of the adepti in Liyue. With a lonely past, she seeks human connection. As a Support, Shenhe boosts Cryo damage and provides buffs for the team.

name: Xinyan
about: Xinyan is a Pyro character in Genshin Impact, a rock musician from Liyue. Energetic and passionate, she brings music to the masses. As a Sub-DPS, Xinyan deals Pyro damage and provides shields, supporting Overload teams.

name: Yun Jin
about: Yun Jin is a Geo character in Genshin Impact, an opera performer in Liyue. Talented and cultured, she preserves Liyue's traditions. As a Support, Yun Jin boosts normal attack damage and provides team buffs.

name: Arataki Itto
about: Arataki Itto is a Geo character in Genshin Impact, the leader of the Arataki Gang in Inazuma. Boisterous and proud, he is a powerful Oni. As a Main DPS, Itto deals massive Geo damage with charged attacks and energy stacks.

name: Gorou
about: Gorou is a Geo character in Genshin Impact, a general of the Watatsumi resistance in Inazuma. Loyal and brave, he supports his allies. As a Support, Gorou boosts Geo damage and provides buffs for Geo teams.

name: Kamisato Ayato
about: Kamisato Ayato is a Hydro character in Genshin Impact, the head of the Kamisato Clan in Inazuma. Wise and composed, he handles political affairs. As a Main DPS, Ayato deals strong Hydro damage with rapid attacks.

name: Kujou Sara
about: Kujou Sara is an Electro character in Genshin Impact, a general of the Tenryou Commission in Inazuma. Loyal and disciplined, she serves the Raiden Shogun. As a Support, Sara boosts damage and restores energy for the team.

name: Sangonomiya Kokomi
about: Sangonomiya Kokomi is a Hydro character in Genshin Impact, the Divine Priestess of Watatsumi Island in Inazuma. Strategic and wise, she leads the resistance. As a Support, Kokomi provides healing and Hydro application for reactions.

name: Shikanoin Heizou
about: Shikanoin Heizou is an Anemo character in Genshin Impact, a detective of the Tenryou Commission in Inazuma. Clever and perceptive, he solves cases with ease. As a Main DPS, Heizou deals Anemo damage with melee attacks and Swirl reactions.

name: Yoimiya
about: Yoimiya is a Pyro character in Genshin Impact, the owner of Naganohara Fireworks in Inazuma. Cheerful and kind, she spreads joy with her fireworks. As a Main DPS, Yoimiya deals strong Pyro damage with rapid bow attacks.

name: Alhaitham
about: Alhaitham is a Dendro character in Genshin Impact, the Scribe of the Sumeru Akademiya. Sharp-witted and independent, he prefers working alone. As a Main DPS, Alhaitham deals powerful Dendro damage with his attacks and abilities.

name: Candace
about: Candace is a Hydro character in Genshin Impact, the guardian of Aaru Village in Sumeru. Loyal and protective, she defends her community. As a Support, Candace provides shields and boosts normal attack damage.

name: Collei
about: Collei is a Dendro character in Genshin Impact, a Forest Ranger trainee in Sumeru. Overcoming a troubled past, she strives to live positively. As a Sub-DPS, Collei deals off-field Dendro damage and supports Bloom reactions.

name: Cyno
about: Cyno is an Electro character in Genshin Impact, the General Mahamatra of the Sumeru Akademiya. Stern and just, he upholds the law. As a Main DPS, Cyno deals powerful Electro damage with Aggravate reactions.

name: Dehya
about: Dehya is a Pyro character in Genshin Impact, a mercenary of the Eremites in Sumeru. Fierce and protective, she stands by her allies. As a Sub-DPS, Dehya deals Pyro damage and mitigates damage for the team.

name: Dori
about: Dori is an Electro character in Genshin Impact, a merchant in Sumeru. Cunning and profit-driven, she seeks business opportunities. As a Support, Dori provides healing and energy regeneration, aiding Aggravate teams.

name: Kaveh
about: Kaveh is a Dendro character in Genshin Impact, a renowned architect in Sumeru. Artistic and often broke, he faces financial struggles. As a Sub-DPS, Kaveh deals Dendro damage and supports Bloom reactions.

name: Tighnari
about: Tighnari is a Dendro character in Genshin Impact, a Forest Ranger leader in Sumeru. Knowledgeable in botany, he protects the rainforest. As a Main DPS, Tighnari deals strong Dendro damage with charged shots.

name: Arlecchino
about: Arlecchino is a Pyro character in Genshin Impact, one of the Eleven Fatui Harbingers and director of the House of the Hearth in Fontaine. Enigmatic and formidable, she is a skilled fighter. As a Main DPS, Arlecchino deals massive Pyro damage with swift attacks.

name: Charlotte
about: Charlotte is a Cryo character in Genshin Impact, a reporter for The Steambird in Fontaine. Curious and determined, she chases stories. As a Support, Charlotte provides healing and applies Cryo, aiding Freeze teams.

name: Chevreuse
about: Chevreuse is a Pyro character in Genshin Impact, the captain of Fontaine's Special Patrol. Strict and just, she maintains order. As a Support, Chevreuse boosts Overload teams and provides healing.

name: Freminet
about: Freminet is a Cryo character in Genshin Impact, a diver of the House of the Hearth in Fontaine. Shy and mechanical, he loves tinkering. As a Sub-DPS, Freminet deals Cryo damage and supports Freeze or physical damage teams.

name: Lynette
about: Lynette is an Anemo character in Genshin Impact, Lyney's magic assistant in Fontaine. Quiet and reserved, she is part of the House of the Hearth. As a Sub-DPS, Lynette deals off-field Anemo damage and supports Swirl reactions.

name: Sigewinne
about: Sigewinne is a Hydro character in Genshin Impact, the head nurse of the Fortress of Meropide in Fontaine. Kind and caring, she tends to prisoners. As a Support, Sigewinne provides healing and boosts team damage.

name: Wriothesley
about: Wriothesley is a Cryo character in Genshin Impact, the Administrator of the Fortress of Meropide in Fontaine. Tough and resolute, he enforces order. As a Main DPS, Wriothesley deals strong Cryo damage with melee attacks.

name: Chasca
about: Chasca is an Anemo character in Genshin Impact, a warrior from Natlan. With a dynamic fighting style, she wields a bow in combat. As a Main DPS, Chasca deals powerful Anemo damage and supports Swirl reactions.

name: Iansan
about: Iansan is an Electro character in Genshin Impact, a member of Natlan's warriors. Strong and determined, she aids her allies in battle. As a Support, Iansan applies Electro and boosts damage for elemental reactions.

name: Kachina
about: Kachina is a Geo character in Genshin Impact, a young warrior of the Nanatzcayan tribe in Natlan. Cheerful and brave, she fights for her people. As a Support, Kachina provides shields and applies Geo, aiding Crystallize teams.

name: Zhongli
about: Zhongli is a Geo character in Genshin Impact, the Geo Archon Morax of Liyue. Wise and knowledgeable, he lives as a mortal. As a Support, Zhongli provides durable shields and reduces enemy resistances, fitting any team composition.
